:'''Asta:''' I often hear the researchers praise you for your resourcefulness and good judgment. What do you think? Any clue what this message is about?
:<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_2010801_16-->
:<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_2010801_16-->
:{{DIcon|Talk}} It seems like something from the Department of Implement Arts.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_201080110-->
::'''Asta:''' Yes, only the researcher called Wen in the Department of Implement Arts would speak like that.
::'''Asta:''' However, it was a strange story how I got hold of this letter at the beginning. It was sandwiched in a tome called ''A Guide to Astral Realm Species'' on the Conference Room table. Normally, no one looks at it except me.
::'''Asta:''' Obviously, someone wanted to hand me this letter in private, so I didn't dare to ask the staff in the Department of Implement Arts.
:;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:{{DIcon|Talk}} Who is this Cryptologist From Locus Silentii?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_201080114-->
::'''Asta:''' As far as I know, there is no one with this title in the space station. It must be an alias.
::'''Asta:''' But the identity of the writer is not what I am most concerned about.
:;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Spirit sounds particularly familiar.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_201080117-->
::'''Asta:''' Spirit... Spirit... Can it be... The Xenohydro? Well done, (Trailblazer)! You just found the "key" to the text right away. Now everything makes sense!
::'''Asta:''' It seems this is no ordinary letter, it's from an informant. Their intention is to report on the Xenohydro.
::'''Asta:''' The Xenohydro has disappeared from the space station since it escaped from Mr. Wen Mingde's hands.
::'''Asta:''' This letter seems to support the rumor that the Xenohydro was not caught because it has an accomplice.
::'''Asta:''' Look at this sentence. "An inquiry into spirit traces, a glance into the site of storage" is obviously leading us to investigate the Xenohydro's range of activities, and "to be an accomplice" implies the existence of an accomplice.
::'''Asta:''' As for the other six sentences, in my opinion, some depict the portrait of the accomplice and some describe the real hiding place of the Xenohydro. Unfortunately, I have no idea how to interpret the rest of the message.
::'''Asta:''' Now that we are done with other work, this letter falls into our hands at just the right moment. It's high time we put the Xenohydro issue back on the table. (Trailblazer), what do you think?
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_2010801_33-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_2010801_33-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I am with you all the way!
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_201080124-->
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I have a lot going on lately...
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_201080126-->
:::'''Asta:''' Please, (Trailblazer). I hope you won't refuse. After all&mdash;
::'''Asta:''' Considering there may be a traitor among us, if I hand this case to our staff, we might alert the culprit. And (Trailblazer), you're not a staff member, and you've also met the Xenohydro before. You really are the ideal candidate to handle this case.
::'''Asta:''' And if there is an accomplice involved, this matter is no longer a simple case of Curio retrieval. It must be handled with caution. Therefore, I would like to ask you to go to the Storage Zone mentioned in the letter and verify the facts.
::'''Asta:''' If we can catch either the Xenohydro or the accomplice, we'll be able to interrogate them. Then I can judge whether the accomplice's motive is malicious or not.
::'''Asta:''' At this critical juncture, it is up to us to finally finish Project Revival.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: ALL_TALK_END-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: ALL_TALK_END-->
::<!--Ends the current performance-->
