:::::{{DIcon|Talk}} Is the damage to the space station serious?
::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100040350_1-->
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 6 asta 103.ogg}} '''Asta:''' Madam Herta gave me a piece of code, which she apparently wrote on the way here. I just tried it out and the defense shield's regenerating three times faster than before.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 6 asta 104.ogg}} '''Asta:''' Thanks to her, the Antimatter Legion outside is not much of a threat anymore. The space station's repairs and reconstruction can also begin smoothly, but internally...
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 6 asta 105.ogg}} '''Asta:''' When the Stellaron was extracted, even for that brief moment, it corroded the space station and formed a new space &mdash; what we now call the Fragmentum.
::::::{{A|VO chapter0 6 asta 106.ogg}} '''Asta:''' The part that was corroded is irreversible, so the space station will always be in a state of quasi-Fragmentum.
::::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} What are the effects of the Fragmentum?
:::::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_100040355_1-->
:::::::{{A|VO chapter0 6 asta 107.ogg}} '''Asta:''' All existing Fragmentums are connected, so there will be monsters that will enter the space station through its Fragmentum.
:::::::{{A|VO chapter0 6 asta 110.ogg}} '''Asta:''' I talked with Arlan and there's no easy solution to this problem at the moment. We can only increase the security and patrol frequency to protect the ongoing research.
::::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
